1
00:00:03,832 --> 00:00:07,907
The people who deny 
the existence of God

2
00:00:07,907 --> 00:00:11,164
or believe that you can’t prove
that God exists,

3
00:00:11,164 --> 00:00:16,110
they believe all kinds of other things
that you can’t prove,

4
00:00:16,110 --> 00:00:20,156
and they don’t apply the same sort
of analysis to those things.

5
00:00:20,450 --> 00:00:22,817
[Is Your Wife a Quark?]

6
00:00:23,178 --> 00:00:30,648
That police officer 
who was with his superior,

7
00:00:30,648 --> 00:00:33,294
they were visiting the Math,

8
00:00:33,294 --> 00:00:37,585
and as I’ve mentioned 
sometimes,

9
00:00:37,585 --> 00:00:41,376
every Bengali’s got 
a little guru in them.

10
00:00:41,376 --> 00:00:42,616
[Laughing]

11
00:00:42,616 --> 00:00:48,373
And they want to show they know Vedānta
or they’re philosophical,

12
00:00:48,379 --> 00:00:54,243
so they like to get an opportunity
to demonstrate it …

13
00:00:54,243 --> 00:00:57,753
or that they’re up 
on the latest scientific theory.

14
00:00:57,753 --> 00:01:01,182
So, we had 
a little discussion

15
00:01:01,182 --> 00:01:04,638
going perhaps about the subjective
evolution of consciousness,

16
00:01:04,638 --> 00:01:06,767
and the one man
says to me,

17
00:01:06,767 --> 00:01:10,691
“It’s all quarks.
Everything’s just quarks.

18
00:01:10,691 --> 00:01:14,735
That’s all.
Everything’s quarks.”

19
00:01:14,735 --> 00:01:21,125
And I said, “Oh, really?
Is your wife a quark?”

20
00:01:21,125 --> 00:01:23,085
[Expressing confusion]

21
00:01:23,085 --> 00:01:25,610
And his boss went, 
“Ha–ha!”

22
00:01:25,610 --> 00:01:29,713
Because he must have to deal
with this man every day.

23
00:01:29,713 --> 00:01:31,878
And he said, “Ha–ha!”

24
00:01:31,878 --> 00:01:36,838
And I said, “Because
if your wife is a quark …”

25
00:01:36,838 --> 00:01:39,584
because he went, 
“Oh–oh, yes!”

26
00:01:39,584 --> 00:01:43,601
I said, “Oh, she’ll be very unhappy
to hear that.”

27
00:01:43,601 --> 00:01:47,798
And he was perplexed 
what to do.

28
00:01:48,729 --> 00:01:53,232
So, my point 
in introducing this is—

29
00:01:53,232 --> 00:01:57,984
there’s all these criteria
they want to apply

30
00:01:57,984 --> 00:02:03,284
to prove or deny 
the existence of God,

31
00:02:03,284 --> 00:02:06,959
but when it comes
to things like love,

32
00:02:06,959 --> 00:02:08,318
which cannot be proved,

33
00:02:08,318 --> 00:02:10,816
they will say that they love
their wives, their children,

34
00:02:10,816 --> 00:02:16,863
their dog, their school,
their university, whatever.

35
00:02:17,279 --> 00:02:22,069
And humour is subjective:

36
00:02:22,071 --> 00:02:26,847
someone’s laughing hysterically,

37
00:02:26,847 --> 00:02:30,714
and someone else
is not cracking a smile.

38
00:02:30,714 --> 00:02:35,892
They say, “Well, I don’t find that funny
at all, I find it insulting.”

39
00:02:35,892 --> 00:02:41,102
So, many things have got
the subjective aspect.

